## Tips

1. **Start with simpler components** - Components with fewer sub-components are easier to migrate first
2. **Test incrementally** - Build and test after each major change
3. **Refer to Base UI docs** - Check <https://base-ui.com> for API details
4. **Use existing patterns** - Follow the action-bar implementation
5. **Check for circular dependencies** - Define types after component definitions when needed
6. **Watch for BaseUIEvent** - Let Base UI components handle their own event types
7. **data-* always go in `state`** - Never put `data-*` directly in `mergeProps`; use the `state` object
8. **Check for HTML attribute conflicts** - Custom props like `onError`, `onSubmit` may clash with `HTMLAttributes`; use `Omit` to resolve
9. **Radix HoverCard ≠ Base UI HoverCard** - Base UI calls it `PreviewCard` with a structurally different API
10. **Migrate utilities as needed** - When components depend on utilities (portal, presence, etc.), migrate those utilities first or use radix versions temporarily
11. **Type organization** - Keep `types/radix/utilities.ts` and `types/base/utilities.ts` separate, update docs to reference the correct base
